Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_socv_constraint_config(25.10)            set_socv_constraint_config(25.10)

Name
       set_socv_constraint_config -

       Enhances  the  built-in  sigma  pessimism of check values for setup and
       hold constraints in the library

Syntax
       set_socv_constraint_config

        [-help]

        [-hold_folding <float>]

        -libs <string>

        [-nochange_hold_folding <float>]

       [-nochange_setup_folding <float>]

        [-setup_folding <float>]

       Enhances the built-in sigma pessimism of check  values  for  setup  and
       hold  constraints  in the library. The folding factor attribute records
       the amount of on-chip-variation pessimism added during cell characteri-
       zation to the nominal setup/hold tables in the libraries.  The  folding
       factor attributes are library level attributes.

       Notes

              * The set_socv_constraint_config command does not reset the tim-
                ing; so it should be used before the report_timing command.

              * To  change  the setting later in the flow, you need to use the
                update_timing -full command.

              * You cannot use this command, if any of  the  following  global
                variables are specified:

                timing_library_setup_sigma_multiplier

                timing_library_hold_sigma_multiplier

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -hold_folding <float>
              Specifies a number of additional sigma units added on top of the
              existing nominal hold value.

              Min = -100

              Max = 100

       -libs <string>
              Specifies a list of library names (not library paths) or collec-
              tion objects.

       -nochange_hold_folding <float>
              Specifies a number of additional sigma units added on top of the
              existing nominal hold value for no-change timing arcs.

              Min = -100

              Max = 100

       -nochange_setup_folding <float>
              Specifies a number of additional sigma units added on top of the
              existing nominal setup value for no-change timing arcs.

              Min = -100

              Max = 100

       -setup_folding <float>
              Specifies a number of additional sigma units added on top of the
              existing nominal setup value.

              Min = -100

              Max = 100

       Examples
              * The  following command is used when an additional margin of 10
                sigma units is applied to the nominal hold tables in  the  li-
                brary collection test.lib:

                set_socv_constraint_config  -hold_folding  10  -libs [get_libs
                test.lib]

Related Information
              * report_timing

              * update_timing

